   "source": [
    "# Hypothesis\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "After deliberation, we predict that Gender and Class will have had the most effect on any individual on the Titanic’s survival, and consequently the associated significance statistics and weight on any model will be largest. \n",
    "\n",
    "For the gender characteristic, we believe that the use of “Women and Children first” or the WCF order, during the Titanic’s sinking had a major positive impact on the survival rates of Females and Passengers that would fit the “Children” characteristic. \n",
    "\n",
    "For the socioeconomic aspect, we believe that the type of ticket, reflecting the class of the individual who purchased the ticket, will have a positive correlation with their associated survival rate. This, we agreed on, will be due to a number of factors, primarily a prevailing classism present during the time period, as well as a number of physical characteristics such as the location of second and third class passengers being lower on the Titanic compared to first class passengers.\n",
    "Instructions: REPLACE the contents of this cell with your work, including any updates to recover points lost in your proposal feedback"
